    "body": "## Problem\r\nCombination of default 'signcolumn' = 'auto' and diagnostic signs that use text causes the sign column to appear and disappear, which shifts buffer content.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nRemove default values for `vim.diagnostic.Opts.Signs.text` and use `numhl` instead. Add `DiagnosticLineNr*` hl-groups linked to `Diagnostic*` groups.\r\n\r\nResult with 'number' enabled:\r\n<img width=\"3024\" height=\"1785\" alt=\"Screenshot\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a692cf49-1490-4586-9794-7d961ad4d4d9\" />\r\n\r\nFix #26078\r\nRelated #38313\r\nBased on @mfussenegger's suggestion: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/26078#issuecomment-4102886772",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
