            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "But there would still be a `vim.diagnostic.Opts.Signs.numhl` table that lets you change linenumber highlights independently of the `DiagnosticSign*` groups. For me it seems the only reason those groups weren't defined before is that `numhl` wasn't used by default.\r\n\r\nTBH I don't understand why the `numhl` and `linehl` tables need to accept hl-group names - isn't that supposed to be done via default hl-groups that user can redefine, instead of doing this via Lua API?",
            "commit_id": "de91b6b0558b9abd00b344645c1e06108a566c5d",
            "created_at": "2026-03-23T15:40:15Z",
