        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> So that means you _won't_ get diagnostic signs by default, then? Isn't that rather a big regression?\r\n\r\nYes, because neither 'number' nor 'signcolumn' are enabled by default, so users must enable them to see some diagnostic signs. Showing them optionally actually worsens the experience. Just from the recent, take a look at this issue bug report demo (#38433). Buffer content shifts on startup, shifts again when you start typing, and keeps toggling - which gets worse with font size increasing.\r\nForcing users to set an option to avoid bad behavior is worse than making the feature opt-in. Most users enable one or both of those options anyway.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-23T15:22:23Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38441#issuecomment-4111465144",
            "id": 4111465144,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/38441",
